quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  26,176,"The companions (i.e., inhabitants) of the Thicket cried lies to the Emissaries"
  26,177,"As Shuaayb said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,178,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,179,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,180,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,181,"Fill up the measure, and do not be of them who make others losers"
  26,182,And weigh with the straight equitableness
  26,183,"And do not depreciate for mankind (the value) of their things, (i.e., their goods) and do not perpetrate (mischief) in the earth (as) corruptors"
  26,184,And be pious to Him Who created you and the earliest crowds
  26,185,"They said, \"Surely you are only one of the utterly bewitched"
  26,186,"And in no way are you (anything) except a mortal, like us, and decidedly we surmise that you are indeed one of the liars"
  26,187,"So let fall down on us lumps from the heaven, in case you are of the sincere"
  26,188,"He said, \"My Lord knows best whatever you do"
  26,189,Yet they cried him lies; then the torment of the Day of the Overshadowing took them (away); surely it was the torment of a Tremendous Day
  26,190,"Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,191,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"